$$ {K}_d=\left[ Ag\cdot Ag\right]/\left[ Ag\right] $$
\end{document}Kd=[Ag⋅Ag]/[Ag]
where K
d is the dissociation constant, [Ag ⋅ Ag] is the concentration of the antigen–antibody complex, [Ag] is the antigen concentration, and [Ab] is the antibody concentration.
